Licensing — The Engineer's Lab Notebooks
=======================================

Copyright (c) 2026 Aymix

This repository is dual-licensed. Which licence applies depends on which part
of the repository you are using. It applies identically to both volumes:

    backend/    Volume I  — The Backend Engineer's Lab Notebook
    devops/     Volume II — The DevOps Engineer's Lab Notebook


1. THE CODE — MIT Licence  (see LICENSE-CODE)
---------------------------------------------
The LaTeX design system and build machinery, in either volume:

    */preamble.tex      the design system: colours, callout boxes, code boxes,
                        diagram styles, chapter opener, layout macros
    */main.tex          the master document / build entry point
    .gitignore

You may use, copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense and sell
these files, including commercially, under the terms of the MIT Licence.
Reuse the design system for your own book or documentation freely.


2. THE CONTENT — CC BY-NC-ND 4.0  (see LICENSE-CONTENT)
-------------------------------------------------------
The workbooks themselves — all written material, exercises, labs, diagrams and
the compiled books:

    */chapters/*.tex    the fourteen chapters of each volume
    */frontmatter.tex   cover, how-to-use, callout legend, the 14-day arc
    */appendix.tex      interview cheat sheet, build tracker, glossary
    */*.pdf             the compiled workbooks
    README.md

Licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives 4.0
International. You may share the workbooks for non-commercial purposes with
attribution, but you may not sell them or distribute modified versions.


In short
--------
Build your own book with the design system. Read, share and study the
workbooks, but do not sell them or republish altered versions of them.

Individual source files carry an SPDX-License-Identifier comment stating which
licence governs that file.
